<Link id="l00381" /><CodeLine lineNumber="381"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// A file system that allows overlaying one \\p AbstractFileSystem on top</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00382" /><CodeLine lineNumber="382"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// of another.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00383" /><CodeLine lineNumber="383"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00384" /><CodeLine lineNumber="384"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// Consists of a stack of &gt;=1 \\p FileSystem objects, which are treated as being</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00385" /><CodeLine lineNumber="385"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// one merged file system. When there is a directory that exists in more than</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00386" /><CodeLine lineNumber="386"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// one file system, the \\p OverlayFileSystem contains a directory containing</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00387" /><CodeLine lineNumber="387"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// the union of their contents.  The attributes (permissions, etc.) of the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00388" /><CodeLine lineNumber="388"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// top-most (most recently added) directory are used.  When there is a file</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00389" /><CodeLine lineNumber="389"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// that exists in more than one file system, the file in the top-most file</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00390" /><CodeLine lineNumber="390"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// system overrides the other(s).</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00582" /><CodeLine lineNumber="582"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00583" /><CodeLine lineNumber="583"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// Here hard links are not intended to be fully equivalent to the classical</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00584" /><CodeLine lineNumber="584"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// filesystem. Both the hard link and the file share the same buffer and</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00675" /><CodeLine lineNumber="675"><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">class </span><span class="doxyHighlight"><a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/vfs/redirectingfilesystemparser">RedirectingFileSystemParser</a>;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00676" /><CodeLine lineNumber="676"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00677" /><CodeLine lineNumber="677"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// A virtual file system parsed from a YAML file.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00678" /><CodeLine lineNumber="678"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00679" /><CodeLine lineNumber="679"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// Currently, this class allows creating virtual files and directories. Virtual</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00680" /><CodeLine lineNumber="680"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// files map to existing external files in \\c ExternalFS, and virtual</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00681" /><CodeLine lineNumber="681"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// directories may either map to existing directories in \\c ExternalFS or list</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00682" /><CodeLine lineNumber="682"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// their contents in the form of other virtual directories and/or files.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00683" /><CodeLine lineNumber="683"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00684" /><CodeLine lineNumber="684"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// The basic structure of the parsed file is:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00685" /><CodeLine lineNumber="685"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// \\verbatim</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00686" /><CodeLine lineNumber="686"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00687" /><CodeLine lineNumber="687"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   &#39;version&#39;: &lt;version number&gt;,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00688" /><CodeLine lineNumber="688"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   &lt;optional configuration&gt;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00689" /><CodeLine lineNumber="689"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   &#39;roots&#39;: &#91;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00690" /><CodeLine lineNumber="690"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///              &lt;directory entries&gt;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00691" /><CodeLine lineNumber="691"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///            &#93;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00692" /><CodeLine lineNumber="692"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// &#125;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00693" /><CodeLine lineNumber="693"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// \\endverbatim</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00694" /><CodeLine lineNumber="694"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// The roots may be absolute or relative. If relative they will be made</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00695" /><CodeLine lineNumber="695"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// absolute against either current working directory or the directory where</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00696" /><CodeLine lineNumber="696"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// the Overlay YAML file is located, depending on the &#39;root-relative&#39;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00697" /><CodeLine lineNumber="697"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// configuration.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00698" /><CodeLine lineNumber="698"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00699" /><CodeLine lineNumber="699"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// All configuration options are optional.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00700" /><CodeLine lineNumber="700"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   &#39;case-sensitive&#39;: &lt;boolean, default=(true for Posix, false for Windows)&gt;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00701" /><CodeLine lineNumber="701"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   &#39;use-external-names&#39;: &lt;boolean, default=true&gt;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00702" /><CodeLine lineNumber="702"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   &#39;root-relative&#39;: &lt;string, one of &#39;cwd&#39; or &#39;overlay-dir&#39;, default=&#39;cwd&#39;&gt;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00703" /><CodeLine lineNumber="703"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   &#39;overlay-relative&#39;: &lt;boolean, default=false&gt;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00704" /><CodeLine lineNumber="704"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   &#39;fallthrough&#39;: &lt;boolean, default=true, deprecated - use &#39;redirecting-with&#39;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00705" /><CodeLine lineNumber="705"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///                   instead&gt;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00706" /><CodeLine lineNumber="706"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   &#39;redirecting-with&#39;: &lt;string, one of &#39;fallthrough&#39;, &#39;fallback&#39;, or</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00707" /><CodeLine lineNumber="707"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///                        &#39;redirect-only&#39;, default=&#39;fallthrough&#39;&gt;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00708" /><CodeLine lineNumber="708"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00709" /><CodeLine lineNumber="709"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// To clarify, &#39;root-relative&#39; option will prepend the current working</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00710" /><CodeLine lineNumber="710"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// directory, or the overlay directory to the &#39;roots-&gt;name&#39; field only if</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00711" /><CodeLine lineNumber="711"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// &#39;roots-&gt;name&#39; is a relative path. On the other hand, when &#39;overlay-relative&#39;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00712" /><CodeLine lineNumber="712"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// is set to &#39;true&#39;, external paths will always be prepended with the overlay</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00713" /><CodeLine lineNumber="713"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// directory, even if external paths are not relative paths. The</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00714" /><CodeLine lineNumber="714"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// &#39;root-relative&#39; option has no interaction with the &#39;overlay-relative&#39;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00715" /><CodeLine lineNumber="715"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// option.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00716" /><CodeLine lineNumber="716"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00717" /><CodeLine lineNumber="717"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// Virtual directories that list their contents are represented as</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00718" /><CodeLine lineNumber="718"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// \\verbatim</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00719" /><CodeLine lineNumber="719"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00720" /><CodeLine lineNumber="720"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   &#39;type&#39;: &#39;directory&#39;,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00721" /><CodeLine lineNumber="721"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   &#39;name&#39;: &lt;string&gt;,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00722" /><CodeLine lineNumber="722"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   &#39;contents&#39;: &#91; &lt;file or directory entries&gt; &#93;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00723" /><CodeLine lineNumber="723"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// &#125;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00724" /><CodeLine lineNumber="724"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// \\endverbatim</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00725" /><CodeLine lineNumber="725"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// The default attributes for such virtual directories are:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00726" /><CodeLine lineNumber="726"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// \\verbatim</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00727" /><CodeLine lineNumber="727"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// MTime = now() when created</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00728" /><CodeLine lineNumber="728"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// Perms = 777</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00729" /><CodeLine lineNumber="729"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// User = Group = 0</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00730" /><CodeLine lineNumber="730"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// Size = 0</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00731" /><CodeLine lineNumber="731"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// UniqueID = unspecified unique value</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00732" /><CodeLine lineNumber="732"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// \\endverbatim</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00733" /><CodeLine lineNumber="733"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// When a path prefix matches such a directory, the next component in the path</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00734" /><CodeLine lineNumber="734"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// is matched against the entries in the &#39;contents&#39; array.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00735" /><CodeLine lineNumber="735"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00736" /><CodeLine lineNumber="736"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// Re-mapped directories, on the other hand, are represented as</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00737" /><CodeLine lineNumber="737"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// /// \\verbatim</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00738" /><CodeLine lineNumber="738"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00739" /><CodeLine lineNumber="739"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   &#39;type&#39;: &#39;directory-remap&#39;,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00740" /><CodeLine lineNumber="740"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   &#39;name&#39;: &lt;string&gt;,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00741" /><CodeLine lineNumber="741"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   &#39;use-external-name&#39;: &lt;boolean&gt;, # Optional</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00742" /><CodeLine lineNumber="742"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   &#39;external-contents&#39;: &lt;path to external directory&gt;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00743" /><CodeLine lineNumber="743"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// &#125;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00744" /><CodeLine lineNumber="744"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// \\endverbatim</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00745" /><CodeLine lineNumber="745"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// and inherit their attributes from the external directory. When a path</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00746" /><CodeLine lineNumber="746"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// prefix matches such an entry, the unmatched components are appended to the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00747" /><CodeLine lineNumber="747"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// &#39;external-contents&#39; path, and the resulting path is looked up in the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00748" /><CodeLine lineNumber="748"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// external file system instead.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00749" /><CodeLine lineNumber="749"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00750" /><CodeLine lineNumber="750"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// Re-mapped files are represented as</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00751" /><CodeLine lineNumber="751"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// \\verbatim</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00752" /><CodeLine lineNumber="752"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00753" /><CodeLine lineNumber="753"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   &#39;type&#39;: &#39;file&#39;,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00754" /><CodeLine lineNumber="754"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   &#39;name&#39;: &lt;string&gt;,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00755" /><CodeLine lineNumber="755"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   &#39;use-external-name&#39;: &lt;boolean&gt;, # Optional</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00756" /><CodeLine lineNumber="756"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   &#39;external-contents&#39;: &lt;path to external file&gt;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00757" /><CodeLine lineNumber="757"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// &#125;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00758" /><CodeLine lineNumber="758"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// \\endverbatim</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00759" /><CodeLine lineNumber="759"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// Their attributes and file contents are determined by looking up the file at</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00760" /><CodeLine lineNumber="760"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// their &#39;external-contents&#39; path in the external file system.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00761" /><CodeLine lineNumber="761"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00762" /><CodeLine lineNumber="762"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// For &#39;file&#39;, &#39;directory&#39; and &#39;directory-remap&#39; entries the &#39;name&#39; field may</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00763" /><CodeLine lineNumber="763"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// contain multiple path components (e.g. /path/to/file). However, any</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00764" /><CodeLine lineNumber="764"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// directory in such a path that contains more than one child must be uniquely</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00765" /><CodeLine lineNumber="765"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// represented by a &#39;directory&#39; entry.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00766" /><CodeLine lineNumber="766"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00767" /><CodeLine lineNumber="767"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// When the &#39;use-external-name&#39; field is set, calls to \\a vfs::File::status()</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00768" /><CodeLine lineNumber="768"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// give the external (remapped) filesystem name instead of the name the file</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00769" /><CodeLine lineNumber="769"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// was accessed by. This is an intentional leak through the \\a</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00770" /><CodeLine lineNumber="770"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// RedirectingFileSystem abstraction layer. It enables clients to discover</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00771" /><CodeLine lineNumber="771"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// (and use) the external file location when communicating with users or tools</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00772" /><CodeLine lineNumber="772"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// that don&#39;t use the same VFS overlay.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00773" /><CodeLine lineNumber="773"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00774" /><CodeLine lineNumber="774"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// FIXME: &#39;use-external-name&#39; causes behaviour that&#39;s inconsistent with how</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00775" /><CodeLine lineNumber="775"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// &quot;real&quot; filesystems behave. Maybe there should be a separate channel for</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00776" /><CodeLine lineNumber="776"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// this information.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00777" /><CodeLine lineNumber="777" lineLink="/docs/api/classes/llvm/vfs/redirectingfilesystem"><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">class </span><span class="doxyHighlight">RedirectingFileSystem</span></CodeLine>
